parameter.paramdescription: This parameter will be presented as a bit map value. Only the first 13 bits (LSB) are used. Bit 0 (LSB) indicates if CM in DL is used: 0=CM DL not used, 1=CM DL used; Bit 1 indicates if CM in UL is used: 0=CM UL not used, 1=CM in UL used; Bit 2 indicates TTI length if E-DCH is used: 0=10ms TTI (default value for non E-DCH connections), 1=2ms TTI; Bit 3 indicates if the connection is using EL2: 0=Fixed size RLC and MAC-hs used on HS-DSCH (non-EL2), 1=Flexible or fixed size RLC and MAC- ehs on HS-DSCH (EL2). Bit 4 is reserved for 64QAM usage indication. Bits 5 and 6 are used to represent speech category , where: 0= Not applicable (bit pattern ?00?) /*used to be single mode 12.2*/ 1= AMR-NB MM Multi-rate . (bit pattern ?01?) 2= AMR-NB MM Single-rate 12.2 (bit pattern ?10?) Bit 7 is reserved for MIMO; bit=1 means MIMO activated and bit=0 means MIMO deactivated. Bit 8 is reserved for SrbOnHs where: 0=SRB on X/DCH, 1=SRB on X/HS Bit 9 is reserved for SrbOnEul where: 0=SRB on DCH/X, 1=SRB on EUL/X Bit 10 indicates if the connection is a Multi Carrier: 0= Multi Carrier is not present in the connection, 1= Multi Carrier is present in the connection. Bit 11 is spare Bit 12 indicates the usage of CPC, where: 0= CPC not used, 1= CPC used. Bit 13-15 are spare If both Bit 4 and Bit 7 are active at the same time, the combination 64QAM+MIMO is used. The rest of the bits are just spare bits and will always be 0
parameter.paramcomments: NO VALIDITY BIT IS USED. Introduced in rev. AX, P7:I2 by FDI 12/19024-10/FCP1036503. Introduced meaning for bit 3 in rev. BB, P7MD:I5, FDI 53/19024-10/FCP1036503. Reserved Bit 4 (the 5th LSB bit) for 64QAM usage indication in rev. BC, P7:I6, CR WRNae01539. Reserved Bit 5,6 (the 6th, 7th LSB bit) for Coverage based AMR in rev. BC2, P7:I6, FDI 95/19024-10/FCP1036503. and TR WRNae16065 Reserved Bit 7 (the 8th LSB bit) for MIMO in rev. BD, P7:I8, FDI 68/19024-10/FCP1036503. Reserved Bit 8 (the 9th LSB bit) for ROHC in rev. BD, P7:I9, FDI 56/19024-10/FCP1036503. parameter.paramdescription: This parameter will be presented as a bit map value. Only the first 13 bits (LSB) are used. Bit 0 (LSB) indicates if CM in DL is used: 0=CM DL not used, 1=CM DL used; Bit 1 indicates if CM in UL is used: 0=CM UL not used, 1=CM in UL used; Bit 2 indicates TTI length if E-DCH is used: 0=10ms TTI (default value for non E-DCH connections), 1=2ms TTI; Bit 3 indicates if the connection is using EL2: 0=Fixed size RLC and MAC-hs used on HS-DSCH (non-EL2), 1=Flexible or fixed size RLC and MAC- ehs on HS-DSCH (EL2). Bit 4 is reserved for 64QAM usage indication. Bits 5 and 6 are used to represent speech category , where: 0= Not applicable (bit pattern ?00?) /*used to be single mode 12.2*/ 1= AMR-NB MM Multi-rate . (bit pattern ?01?) 2= AMR-NB MM Single-rate 12.2 (bit pattern ?10?) Bit 7 is reserved for MIMO; bit=1 means MIMO activated and bit=0 means MIMO deactivated. Bit 8 is reserved for SrbOnHs where: 0=SRB on X/DCH, 1=SRB on X/HS Bit 9 is reserved for SrbOnEul where: 0=SRB on DCH/X, 1=SRB on EUL/X Bit 10 indicates if the connection is a Multi Carrier: 0= Multi Carrier is not present in the connection, 1= Multi Carrier is present in the connection. Bit 11 is spare Bit 12 indicates the usage of CPC, where: 0= CPC not used, 1= CPC used. Bit 13-15 are spare If both Bit 4 and Bit 7 are active at the same time, the combination 64QAM+MIMO is used. The rest of the bits are just spare bits and will always be 0 The Connection Properties of the UeRc reported in EVENT_PARAM_WANTED_CONF. This parameter is not applicable for IRATHO, IRATCC or GAN HO. For CNHHO this parameter shall report the Connection Properties of the wanted target UeRc for the CNHHO.
